s statistics and special abilities except as noted here.
\par Hit Dice: Increase to d12.
\par Speed: Same as the base creature. If the base creature has a swim speed, the vampire retains the ability to swim and is not vulnerable to immersion in running water (see below).
\par AC: The base creature\rquote s natural armor improves by +6.
\par Attacks: A vampire retains all the attacks of the base creature and also gains a slam attack if it didn\rquote t already have one.
\par Damage: Vampires have slam attacks. If the base creature does not have this attack form, use the damage values in the table below. Creatures with natural attacks retain their old damage ratings or use the values below, whichever is better.
