\par Special Attacks: A vampire retains all the special attacks of the base creature and also gains those listed below. Saves have a DC of 10 + 1/2 vampire\rquote s HD + vampire\rquote s Charisma modifier unless noted otherwise.
\par Domination (Su): A vampire can crush an opponent\rquote s will just by looking onto his or her eyes. This is similar to a gaze attack, except that the vampire must take a standard action, a
nd those merely looking at it are not affected. Anyone the vampire targets must succeed at a Will save or fall instantly under the vampire\rquote 
s influence as though by a dominate person spell cast by a 12th-level sorcerer. The ability has a range of 30 feet.
\par Energy Drain (Su): Living creatures hit by a vampire\rquote s slam attack suffer 2 negative levels.
\par Blood Drain (Ex): A vampire can suck blood from a living victim with its fangs by making a successful grapple check. If it pins the foe, it drains blood, inflicting 1d4 points of permanent Constitution drain each round the pin is maintained.
